# Keep the build context small + reproducible. The Rust build needs the source
# tree (crates/, Cargo.toml, Cargo.lock, build.rs files) but none of these.
#
# Patterns are anchored to the context root (leading `/`) so we never
# accidentally drop a file a crate's build.rs/include_str! depends on deeper in
# the tree (e.g. crate-local *.tsv golden fixtures).
.git
.claude
/.dockerignore

# Build artifacts / target dirs (regenerated in-image).
/target
/target-iso
/.isolated-target
/.iso-target
/.amcheck-target
crates/*/target

# Large top-level catalogs / audits / docs not needed to compile the binary.
/audits
/docs
/ops
/tools
/scripts
/__pycache__
/sock
/*.tsv
/*.log
/*.patch

# Editor / OS cruft.
.DS_Store
